node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text: Think cinnamon rolls are out of your baking wheelhouse? Think again! node.text: Buttercream … without butter? With plant-based butters, it can be done! We’re putting two of the most popular vegan butters to the test with butter-heavy recipes to see how they perform. See the results (including which type of butter went into each layer of this cake!) at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your plant-based bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: Without a peeler, knife, or frustration, you can perfectly peel dozens of peaches in just a few minutes, making cobblers, pies, shortcakes, and more all that much closer to being in your belly. Is it wizardry? No, it’s our own PJ (who really is pretty magical), and she’s here with a quick, easy tip for peeling peaches in a flash. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to see how, and show us your peachy bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Sweet not sugary blueberry muffins in a baking tray and cooling on a rack. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Blueberry-filled mornings are the best — that’s just a fact. This fruity twist on our classic doughnut muffins recipe is sweetened with fresh berries and a bit of our Baking Sugar Alternative for a sweet (but not too sugary) way to start the day. Find the recipe and our full collection of Sweet Not Sugary recipes at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your favorite ways to bake with blueberries with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: Have you ever experienced 60 seconds of such hunger-inducing happiness in your life? We didn’t think so! @emcdowell’s magnificent tower of Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls is a feat of cinnamon and sprinkles we can’t wait to see you all recreate. See how she did it on our blog by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your version with #recipeoftheyear

node.accessibility_caption: Two cupcakes, one sad and melted by the summer heat, the other, perfect. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Pretty sure we can all agree we’ve felt like that cupcake on the left on more than one scorching summer day. Unless you’re going for a trendy “drip” cake look, you probably don’t want your frosting to melt into a pile of buttery despair. With a slew of frosting recipes and a heat gun in hand, @chefsusaninvt is here to figure out which recipes can take the heat. Check out the results at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your summer cakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A tangy ginger and peach sour cream pie served with coffee. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: If you’re looking for a recipe to take fresh summer peaches to new heights, this is the one. Featuring a tangy, rich custard, this peach pie is topped with buttery streusel that's flavored with spicy crystallized ginger. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your peachy bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Bottles of homemade vanilla ready for baking. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Whether on its own or enhancing other flavors, vanilla shines in countless treats and baked goods. Its price point can leave much to be desired, so a favorite project of ours is one you might just make an annual tradition: making homemade vanilla extract! @life.of.kye is here to show you exactly how at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your favorite vanilla bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A loaf of cheesy gluten free bread with two slices cut from the end. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Thanks to the batter-like consistency of #GlutenFree bread dough, our GF Sandwich Bread recipe is perfect for folding and swirling in mix-ins. From apple-cinnamon to sharp cheddar or classic cinnamon swirl, say goodbye to plain gluten-free bread forever! See how it’s done by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your rendition with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A loaf of cheesy gluten free bread with two slices cut from the end. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
A loaf of apple cinnamon gluten free bread with three slices cut from the end. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
Decadent zucchini brownies stacked on a plate. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Is your garden overtaken with giant zucchinis? It is that time of year, after all! You’d be hard-pressed to guess that puréed zucchini is the key to moisture in these ultra-chocolaty fudge brownies. Give the recipe a go by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and show us how you’re baking with zucchini this summer with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Perfectly stackable s’more granola bars. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Without having to trudge into the woods to find a proper roasting stick, enjoy the cozy-campfire flavors of a s’more in these chewy-crunchy granola bars. Loaded with graham cracker crumbs, chocolate, and mini marshmallows, summertime s’mores are just a tap (at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking) away! Share your marshmallow creations with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Bowls of beautiful ice creams on a black surface. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: It feels like a cruel betrayal when homemade ice cream comes out rock hard or oily — not creamy. (“Cream” is right in its name, after all!) To prevent this frozen fumble, our blog (at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking) is dishing up the secrets to making perfect homemade ice cream. Show off your batch with #KingArthurBaking
